1 STATE OF OKLAHOMA
2 2nd Session of the 60th Legislature (2026
3 HOUSE BILL 3019 By: Hays
4
5
6 AS INTRODUCED
7 An Act relating to schools; amending 70 O.S. 2021,
Section 6-127, which relates to teacher's assistants;
8 increasing and reducing class size required to have a
teacher's assistant for specific school years;
9 removing requirement for certain percentage of
reduced lunch eligible students to be present;
10 amending 70 O.S. 2021, Sections 18-113.1 and 18-
133.2, which relate to class size limitations;
11 increasing and reducing the maximum number of
students allowed per class in kindergarten through
12 fifth grades; eliminating certain exceptions to class
size limits; creating class size limitations for
13 classes with teacher's assistants; providing an
effective date; and declaring an emergency.
14
15
16
17 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
18 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 70 O.S. 2021, Section 6-127, is
19 amended to read as follows:
20 Section 6-127. A. Beginning with For the 1990-91 2026-2027
21 school year, every school site shall employ a teacher's assistant or
22 use a volunteer for each class in grades kindergarten through two
23 which has a class size of more than twenty (20) twenty-two (22)
24 students in average daily membership as of September 15 of each year
Req. No. 14157 Page 1

1 and which is composed of students, at least twenty percent (20%) of
2 whom meet the criteria specified in subsection B of this section;
3 provided, this requirement. For the 2027-2028 school year, every
4 school site shall employ a teacher's assistant for each class in
5 kindergarten which has a class size of more than twenty (20)
6 students in average daily membership as of September 15 of each
7 year. Beginning with the 2028-2029 school year, and each school
8 year thereafter, every school site shall employ a teacher's
9 assistant for each class in kindergarten which has a class size of
10 more than eighteen (18) students in average daily membership as of
11 September 15 of each year. The requirements of this subsection
12 shall not apply to classes that are not subject to class size
13 limitations pursuant to subsection D C of Section 18-113.1 of this
14 title or to pull-out sections for Chapter 1 or to Special Education
15 students. Assistants shall be required as of September 15 of each
16 year. The State Board of Education shall establish regulations that
17 prescribe the qualifications for and duties of teacher assistants in
18 public schools. The State Board of Education shall also establish
19 standards and regulations which provide for a determination of how
20 and when teacher assistants may be used as an appropriate and
21 necessary part of classroom instruction. In addition to any other
22 duties which the Board may deem appropriate, teacher assistants may
23 perform or assist a classroom teacher in the performance of hall
24 room duty, bus duty, playground duty, lunchroom duty,
Req. No. 14157 Page 2

1 extr acurricular activities volving involving school functions or any
2 other noninstructional duty the Board may prescribe. Provided,
3 nothing in this section shall construe teacher assistants to be
4 defined as personnel as set out in Section 6-108 of this title or
5 require teacher assistants to possess the certification required for
6 teachers.
7 B. Any student who meets the criteria established by the State
8 Board which are commensurate with established eligibility criteria
9 for participation in the National School Lunch Act of 1946, 42
10 U.S.C. Section 1751 et seq. as amended, shall be included in the
11 percentage necessary to meet the requirement of subsection A of this
12 section for the entitlement to a teacher's assistant for such class
13 Kindergarten classes with a teacher's assistant shall not exceed
14 twenty-eight (28) students; provided, this requirement shall not
15 apply to classes that are not subject to class size limitations
16 pursuant to subsection C of Section 18-113.1 of this title.
17 C. For the purposes of this section, and for Sections 18-113.1
18 and 18-113.2 of this title, a federally funded bilingual assistant
19 shall not qualify as a teacher's assistant. Commented [1]: BDERIV
20 SECTION 2. AMENDATORY 70 O.S. 2021, Section 18-113.1, is
21 amended to read as follows:
22 Section 18-113.1. A. The provisions of this subsection shall
23 apply only to grades one through three five.
24
Req. No. 14157 Page 3

1 1. Except For the 2026-2027 school year, except as otherwise
2 provided for in this section, no child shall be included in the
3 average daily membership of a school district for the purpose of
4 computing and paying state-appropriated funds if that child is
5 regularly assigned to a teacher or to a class that includes more
6 than twenty-two (22) students. For the 2027-2028 school year,
7 except as otherwise provided for in this section, no child shall be
8 included in the average daily membership of a school district for
9 the purpose of computing and paying state-appropriated funds if that
10 child is regularly assigned to a teacher or to a class that includes
11 more than twenty (20) students. Beginning with the 2028-2029 school
12 year, except as otherwise provided for in this section, no child
13 shall be included in the average daily membership of a school
14 district for the purpose of computing and paying state-appropriated
15 funds if that child is regularly assigned to a teacher or to a class
16 that includes more than eighteen (18) students.
17 2. If a class or classes in a grade exceed the class size
18 limitation provided for in this subsection, the class size
19 limitation and penalty shall not apply if:
20 a. the creation of an additional class would cause a
21 class to have fewer than ten (10) students; and
22 b. a full time teacher's assistant, as defined in Section 6-
23 127 of this title, is employed to serve with each teacher in a class
24 that exceeds the class size limitation provided for in this
Req. No. 14157 Page 4

1 subs ection; provided such class sizes shall not exceed twenty-eight
2 (28) students.
3 3. No school district shall be penalized for exceeding class
4 size limitations set forth in this subsection if the limitations are
5 exceeded beginning after the first nine (9) weeks of the school
6 year.
7 Any school district found to be in violation of the provisions
8 of this subsection shall receive a penalty in the State Aid formula
9 as a reduction to State Aid to be determined as follows:
10 a. Multiply each pupil in excess of the class size
11 membership limit as provided in this subsection by the
12 grade level weight and by the Base Foundation Support
13 Level for the current school year, and
14 b. Multiply each pupil in excess of the class size
15 membership limit as provided in this subsection by the
16 grade level weight and by the Incentive Aid guarantee
17 for the current school year times twenty (20), and
18 c. Sum the products of subparagraphs a and b of this
19 paragraph.
20 B. The provisions of this subsection shall apply only to grades
21 four through grade six.
22 1. Except as otherwise provided for in this section, no child
23 shall be included in the average daily membership of a school
24 district for the purpose of computing and paying state-appropriated
Req. No. 14157 Page 5

1 fund s if that child is regularly assigned to a teacher or to a class
2 that includes more than twenty (20) students.
3 2. If a class or classes in a grade exceed the class size
4 limitation provided for in this subsection, the class size
5 limitation and penalty shall not apply if the creation of an
6 additional class would cause a class to have fewer than sixteen (16)
7 students.
8 3. No school district shall be penalized for exceeding class
9 size limitations set forth in this subsection if the limitations are
