1 C. Classes in the following subjects shall not be subject to
2 the class size limitations provided for in subsections A and B of
3 this section:
4 1. Physical education; and
5 2. Chorus, band, orchestra and similar music classes.
6 D. If a school district groups its grades as grades one through
7 five, grades six through eight, and grades nine through twelve, then
8 as to such district the provisions of subsection B of this section
9 shall not apply to grades four and five rather than grades four
10 through grade six, and the provisions of Section 18-113.3 of this
11 title shall apply to grades six through twelve.
12 E. Any violations of the provisions of this section shall
13 result in denial of accreditation in accordance with the
14 requirements of Section 3-104.4 of this title.
15 F. Any school district which at the beginning of the school
16 year does not have sufficient classrooms to meet the class size
17 limitation provided for in this section as determined by guidelines
18 established by the State Board of Education shall not be penalized
19 for failure to meet the class size limitations provided for in this
20 section if:
21 a. the school district has voted indebtedness, at any
22 time within the five (5) years preceding the year the
23 district exceeds the class size limitations or during
24 the year the district exceeds the class size
